## 5. Subscriptions, Payments, and Token Budgets

Certain features of S A P O may require payment, typically through:

- **App stores** (e.g., Apple App Store, and in the future Google Play), and/or  
- **Payment processors** (e.g., Stripe, on supported platforms).

### 5.1 How Payments Work

- Payments, billing, and refunds are generally handled by the **app store** or **payment processor**, **not** directly by us.  
- Their own **terms and privacy notices** govern how they handle your payment information.  
- We receive **limited subscription information** (like plan, status, order/purchase token, and relevant dates) needed to manage your entitlements, as described in the Privacy Policy.

You must review any applicable terms from the app store or processor you use (e.g., Apple Media Services terms, Google Play terms, Stripe terms).

### 5.2 Subscription Renewal and Cancellation

Unless otherwise stated in the app or app store, **paid subscriptions renew automatically** at the end of each billing period and will continue until canceled.

- Your account (for example, your Apple ID or Google account) will be charged for renewal **within 24 hours prior to the end of the current billing period**, at the price shown for your plan at the time of renewal.
- You can **manage or cancel** your subscription at any time in your app store account settings (for example, in the Apple ID or Google Play subscription settings). Deleting the app **does not** cancel your subscription.

If you cancel, you will retain access to subscription features until the end of the current billing period, and the subscription will not renew. You will not receive a refund or credit for partial periods unless required by applicable law or app store rules.

### 5.3 Token Budgets

Each subscription plan includes a **monthly AI token budget** used to process your requests.

- When you use S A P O, your requests **consume tokens** according to your plan.  
- It is your responsibility to understand your plan limits.  

As explained in the Privacy Policy:

- Any **unused portion** of your monthly AI token budget may be used to run **background AI processes** to expand and improve S A P O’s **open phonetic database**, in a privacy-preserving way.  
- Your **private sessions** are not automatically used as identifiable training data for the open phonetic database without specific consent or proper anonymization.

The details of each plan (pricing, token allocation, renewal cycle, etc.) are shown in the app or app store interface and may change over time in accordance with Section 13 (Changes to These Terms and the Service).

### 5.4 Free Tier

S A P O offers a **free tier** that provides ongoing access to a limited set of features at no cost. The free tier may include access to phonetic transliteration, semantic translation, and other functionality, subject to **usage limits and technical restrictions.**

During the current **beta period**, the free tier may include **more generous token allocations** or broader access than what will be offered after beta. Once beta ends, the free tier may include **reduced or more restricted limits**, especially for token-intensive features such as phonetic transliteration.

The free tier:
	- Has its own **token limits**, which may differ substantially from paid plans
	- Is subject to **fair-use protections and rate limits**
	- May include changes in limits, features, or availability as S A P O evolves

We may modify, limit, or discontinue the free tier at any time, in accordance with applicable law and platform rules. Any such changes will not affect an existing paid subscription unless explicitly stated.

### 5.5 Price Changes

We may change the **prices, plans, or features** of S A P O subscriptions from time to time. If we do, the applicable app store or payment processor will generally notify you of any price changes and, where required by law or platform rules, will request your consent before the new price applies to a **renewing** subscription. If you do not agree to a price change, you may cancel your subscription in your app store account settings before the change takes effect.

